	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="subheader">Adding A Leave Type</td></tr>
    <tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">1.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the Add button.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">2.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Insert the Leave Code, Type and Name.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">3.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">
			Select either any, Female, or Male from the Gender column:<br>
			<li>Any - Any gender can apply this leave type.</li>
			<li>Female - Only Female employee can apply this leave type.</li>
			<li>Male - Only Male employees can apply this leave type.</li>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">4.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Credit allowed - Select this option if the leave type to be treated as a credit leave.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">5.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the Submit button.</td>
	</tr>
